If you get the error:

Error occurred when executing SUPIR_sample:

The size of tensor a (48) must match the size of tensor b (128) at non-singleton dimension 3

Make sure you haven't unintentionally selected a Tiled Sampler
if input image is small, upscale to at least 1024x1024 or equivalent res.

nodes.title: CCSR Sampling Methods
widgets_values:
sampling methods:
ccsr = normal, untiled, heavy on VRAM

ccsr_tiled_mixdiff = tiled, each tile decoded separately, has seams

ccsr_tiled_vae_gaussian_weights = seams fixed, can be less accurate and introduce extra noise

If using CCSR: set SUPIR Image Input Switch Node to 1.
If bypassing CCSR: et SUPIR Image Input Switch Node to 2.
Depending on the quality or style/medium of the input image, you may wish to bypass the SUPIR First Stage.... Click on the ? on the node to learn more.

Bypass First Stage Node if not needed, ie does not have a lot of compression artifacts. 

use switch at lower-left of workflow

widgets_values: a man sitting on an armchair with a patterned upholstery. He's wearing a light blue, long-sleeved shirt with a small, visible logo on the left chest area. domestic setting. high quality, detailed, drawing

for images with a lot of compression artefacts0, use supir-v0Q, 
for lightly degraded or images with a lot of detail already it's maybe better to use supir-v0F
if input image is small, it should be upscaled or resized to at least 1024 in either dimension (in multiples of 64). since SUPIR is optimized for SDXL-based models.

Choose input 1 if using CCSR stage.
Choose input 2 if skipping CSSR stage.

Use switch at lower-left of workflow
